    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 13,
    "last_activity_date" : 1736842161,
    "last_edit_date" : 1736842161,
    "creation_date" : 1700151210,
    "answer_id" : 77496400,
    "question_id" : 54205486,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Using gradle, you can turn sharing off:</p>\n<pre><code>tasks.test {\n    //kotlin\n    jvmArgs = listOf(&quot;-Xshare:off&quot;)\n    //groovy\n    jvmArgs &quot;-Xshare:off&quot;;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 894842,
        "reputation" : 3140,
        "user_id" : 932359,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0928ec6a795bff832ea1067a92f284aa?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Luke Usherwood",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/932359/luke-usherwood"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1727864784,
      "post_id" : 78839548,
      "comment_id" : 139377927,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I suggest going to:  Preferences &gt; Installed JREs and setting the &quot;Default VM arguments&quot; to <code>-Xshare:off -XX:+EnableDynamicAgentLoading</code>. This way it applies globally to all new tests run, and the flags can vary per Java version. Hopefully these flags won&#39;t harm debugging other targets."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6114182,
      "reputation" : 345,
      "user_id" : 4769751,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/10153223909213739/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "Oleksandr Potomkin",
