    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1722955258,
    "last_edit_date" : 1722955258,
    "creation_date" : 1722953825,
    "answer_id" : 78839548,
    "question_id" : 54205486,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I want to show Eclipse users how I removed this warning:</p>\n<p>Go to RUN submenu/Run Configurations...<br/>\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pBTdBtGf.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pBTdBtGf.png\" alt=\"Shows the RUN submenu\" /></a></p>\n<p>Then select the tab (x)-Arguments\nand type the -Xshare:off in the VM arguments field<br/><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/1KFMJsp3.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/1KFMJsp3.png\" alt=\"Showa where to type -Xshare:off\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 987285,
      "reputation" : 17565,
      "user_id" : 1005481,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 89,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/cNh9q.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "barfuin",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1005481/barfuin"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1729177328,
    "creation_date" : 1729177328,
    "answer_id" : 79098701,
    "question_id" : 54205486,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just to add to the list of variants: With newer Gradle, using the JVM test suite plugin, the config looks like this:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>testing {\n    suites {\n        test {\n            useJUnitJupiter()  // or whatever\n            targets {\n                all {\n                    testTask.configure {\n                        jvmArgs('-Xshare:off')\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
